alone**, reflecting the integration of xAI (acquired February 2026) and X Holdings (merged March 2025) employee stock plans.\n- The jump from $16M (FY 2024) to $1,063M (FY 2025) corresponds to the retrospective inclusion of X Holdings\' SBC following the common-control recast.\n- By Q1 2026, the AI segment\'s SBC ($378M) exceeded that of Space ($145M) and Connectivity ($116M) **combined**.\n\n---\n\n## 3. AI Segment Depreciation & Amortization\n\n| Period | AI D&A | % of Total Company D&A |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Q1 2026** | **$1,493M** | 61.1% of $2,442M total |\n| **Q1 2025** | **$771M** | 53.4% of $1,443M total |\n| **FY 2025** | **$3,568M** | 53.2% of $6,701M total |\n| **FY 2024** | **$1,679M** | 43.9% of $3,824M total |\n| **FY 2023** | **$1,180M** | 44.8% of $2,635M total |\n\n**Key observations:**\n- D&A more than **tripled** from FY 2023 ($1,180M) to FY 2025 ($3,568M), driven by GPU/server capitalization and data center buildout.\n- The Q1 2026 annualized run-rate (~$6B) suggests continued heavy capital deployment.\n- AI capital expenditures in Q1 2026 alone were **$7,723M** (versus $2,567M in Q1 2025), explaining the accelerating D&A trajectory.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Common-Control Recast Impact of the xAI and X Holdings Mergers\n\n### What the filing discloses:\n\n**Transaction structure:**\n- **X Merger** (March 28, 2025): xAI acquired X Holdings Corp. and X.AI Corp. via share exchange\n- **xAI Merger** (February 2, 2026): SpaceX acquired X.AI Holdings Corp. (xAI) via share exchange\n- Both were accounted for as **reorganizations under common control** because Elon Musk held majority voting interests in SpaceX, xAI, and X throughout all periods presented\n\n**Accounting treatment:**\n- **Retrospective combination** of net assets at their **historical carrying amounts** for all periods presented\n- **No new goodwill or intangible assets** recorded\n- **All intercompany transactions eliminated** in consolidation\n- Capital stock and shareholders\' equity reflects a **continuation of SpaceX\'s historical equity**, combined with X and xAI\'s historical equity as adjusted by exchange ratios\n- xAI\'s redeemable convertible preferred stock through the merger date was **excluded** from combined equity and converted to SpaceX common stock at the xAI Merger date\n- This constitutes a **change in reporting entity** (disclosed per ASC 805)\n\n**Stock split retroactivity:**\n- On May 4, 2026, a **five-for-one forward stock split** was executed\n- All share and per-share data retroactively adjusted for all periods presented\n- Redeemable convertible preferred stock conversion rates proportionately adjusted\n\n### Quantifiable financial impact of the recast:\n\nWhile the filing doesn\'t isolate a single "recast impact" figure, the **before-and-after changes** between FY 2023 and FY 2025 show the scale of integration:\n\n| Metric | FY 2023 (Recast) | FY 2024 (Recast) | FY 2025 (Recast) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| AI Revenue | $2,961M | $2,620M | $3,201M |\n| AI Loss from Ops | $(3,973)M | $(1,561)M | $(6,355)M |\n| AI D&A | $1,180M | $1,679M | $3,568M |\n| AI SBC | $3M | $16M | $1,063M |\n| AI Restructuring | $237M | $213M | $487M |\n| AI Impairment | $3,775M | $0 | $0 |\n| AI CapEx | $463M | $5,633M | $12,727M |\n\n**The most significant recast effects are:**\n1. **Revenue history** now includes X Holdings (formerly Twitter) revenue retroactively, contributing to the ~$3B annual AI segment revenue across all years\n2. **SBC explosion** from $3M to $1,063M reflects the retroactive inclusion of xAI/X equity compensation plans\n3. **CapEx ramp** from $463M (2023) to $12,727M (2025) reflects the combined entity\'s data center infrastructure buildout\n4. The **2023 impairment of $3,775M** appears to relate to X/Twitter write-downs that were part of the pre-merger entity\'s financials\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe AI segment\'s Adjusted EBITDA has been **consistently negative since 2025** after stripping out the 2023 impairment anomaly, driven by massive infrastructure investment (D&A ~$3.6B/year, CapEx ~$12.7B in 2025). SBC is now the largest non-cash adjustment after D&A, reflecting the equity-heavy compensation structure of the combined xAI/X entity. The common-control recast created a **fundamentally different financial picture** by merging what were historically three separate entities into one reporting structure—though no new asset values were recognized, the operational scale of SpaceX is now dramatically larger.',
